  <summary>Specifies the name of the program used to play movies and sounds.</summary>
  <examples>
    <example>set the videoClipPlayer to "/usr/bin/xanim.new"</example>
  </examples>
  <description>
    <p>Use the <b>videoClipPlayer</b> <glossary tag="property">property</glossary> to specify the video player used on <glossary tag="Unix">Unix systems</glossary>.</p><p/><p><b>Value:</b></p><p>The <b>videoClipPlayer</b> is a <keyword tag="string">string</keyword> consisting of the <glossary tag="file path">file path</glossary> of a program.</p><p/><p><b>Comments:</b></p><p>LiveCode uses the program specified by the <b>videoClipPlayer</b> when you use the <command tag="play">play</command> <glossary tag="command">command</glossary>.</p><p/><p>By default, on Unix systems, audio clips and video clips are played with the "xanim" player.</p>
